In a sea of umpteen-percent-ABV hop-bombs, Black Hammer Brewing will create malt-focused, superbly balanced sessionable beers that are based on styles that have persisted since the Reinheitsgebot in 1487. Using their microbrewery and tasting room in the heart of San Francisco as their launch pad, they plan to serve their beer at their taproom, while quickly expanding to a regional presence on the West Coast through strategic brewing and packaging partnerships. LEADING EDGE BREWING TECH They are launching with a diverse skill set and technological approach that is relatively uncommon in the startup craft brewing industry - their team consists of Jim Furman, a skilled chemical/nuclear engineer and brewer, and Kevin Jackey, their CFO and a skilled financial professional. They're employing brewing process control technologies that even most established breweries haven't yet adopted, including proprietary fermentation approaches and gluten-reduction techniques that are only recently gaining traction in the industry. They don't just see brewing as an ancient art, they see it as a science where quality, production and design can be enhanced by new technologies.

It provides online list rental fulfillment and ecommerce software for email and postal mailing lists; and custom data processing services for list and direct marketing professionals. Midpoint CC also provides ListKey 4.0 Professional, an online count and order system with ecommerce functionality for list and data organizations; ListKey 4.0 Storefront for list and data marketers with specialized target marketing-vertical industry-needs and private labeling opportunities; ListKey List Manager for subscriber, response, and survey-based files in a list management environment; ListKey Data Pipe to integrate data and mailing list sales into an existing ecommerce site as print-on-demand, business services, and online direct mail; ListKey 4.0 Data Share that enables owners to share and expand their data distribution via the ListKey owners network of sites; and ListKey Portal that enables to plug and play-start sales and marketing program. It serves data distributors, list owners and brokers, compilers, list managers, aggregators, and businesses with special Internet access needs in the United States and internationally. Midpoint CC, LLC was formerly known as Alvion, LLC and changed its name in September 2008. The company was founded in 1999 and is based in Cape Coral, Florida. As of September 15, 2008, Midpoint CC, LLC operates as a subsidiary of Acxiom Corp.

Description: Price It Here provides purchasing advice for business.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Imagine a business where everyone wins. That’s what they did. They took one look at LendingTree.com and they saw a great way to fill out one form and have mortgage  lenders coming directly to you  with super competitive quotes that match your unique needs. A close look at Hotel.com and they realized an amazing way to find hotels and compare prices anywhere with the click of a button. And even cooler was the fact that neither company required a fee from the consumer. So they thought, this should be done for everything. Phones systems, copiers, payroll service, coffee service, you name it. And better yet, it should all be done from a single website. And PriceItHere.com was born. To many people who first looked at their business model this perfectly fit the definition of insanity, especially considering that their visitors never paid for their service, no memberships were necessary, and they could only earn money when they put an interested buyer together with a qualified seller who was competing with low prices. It took an internet business man and a step of faith, but in 2014,  PriceItHere.com blew up the internet after launching its online buyers guide with just 40 categories, and they knew it was a home run.

Description: BOTY creates channels of communication and engagement at the bar.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: BOTY is changing the post-COVID bar scene to one of meaningful connection & personalization. Our technology empowers bar goers and bar owners to approach the bar experience on a deeper, smarter, and more intentional level. We seek 1 million in funding for product development, customer acquisition, operating costs, and to strategically market. The bar ‘scene’ is fragmented, disjointed, and lacks opportunities for true connection. BOTY provides technology for both the bar goer and bar owner that revolutionizes how people find bars, what they do while at the bar, how they interact with others at the bar, and what keeps them ‘coming back.’ For the bar goer, BOTY allows users to search for bars using very specific criteria, and guides them through their time at the bar: allowing them to ‘check in,’ play trivia, accumulate and then share or give BOTY points (Venmo for bars) and direct message others at the same bar. For the bar owner, BOTY provides in depth real time analytics: who is at the bar, how long they are staying, what they are ordering, etc. Once the patrons leave, BOTY allows the owner to keep in touch in a real -- two-way conversation -- through messaging, surveys and push notifications.
